      "span_text": "Although ceftriaxone can interact with calcium and displace bilirubin from albumin-binding sites, increasing the risk of adverse events, one may still consider use of the drug in the neonatal period due to the considerable CSF concentrations reached.  Thus, it is possible to extend the indications to the youngest patients with primary brain injury, particularly after neurosurgical procedures."
