      "span_text": "Steele et al found ceftriaxone concentrations in the CSF of infants to be 5.4 μg/mL and 6.4 μg/mL after doses of 50 mg/kg and 70 mg/kg, respectively, with CSF to peak serum concentrations of 2.2%-2.3%.  McCracken et al assessed ceftriaxone in newborns weighing less than 1,500 g and observed significant differences ie, the mean plasma half-life was longer and the volume of distribution was larger."
